Johnnie, Jazz & Whisky (#JJW), Nigeria’s premier Afrojazz platform which showcases the best of authentic live performances will be host Afrojazz genius, Lagbaja and award-winning singer, Simi in its fourth edition at the national’s capital, Abuja. The event which kicks off at 7pm on Saturday July 28, 2018 at Central Park Arena, Abuja will have the superstar pair delivering performances in an evening of good conversation, networking and diverse blends of the famous Johnnie Walker Black Label. Foretelling the evening as a night of music and flavours in a promotional video, songstress Simi, says: “I have always wondered what my creamy and tropical flavour would be like if it mixes with Lagbaja’s Smoky feel. I think you and I can find that out at the Johnnie Jazz & Whisky in Abuja.” In its 120 years of existence, Johnnie Walker Black Label has represented the rarest and finest of whiskies thus earning the right as the ‘Everest of Whiskies’. 